org.osate.ge.di

Annotation Type BuildCreateOperation


  • @Documented
 @Target(value=METHOD)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface BuildCreateOperation

    This annotation must not be applied to more than one method per class. When a method with this annotation is executed, it should create an operation for creating the business object.

    Usages

    UsageDescriptionReturn Value
    Business Object HandlerCreates a new business object. Only called when when the method marked CanCreate returns true for the same arguments.The created business object. Object

    Named Parameters

    ParameterUsageDescription
    Names.PALETTE_ENTRY_CONTEXTBusiness Object handlerThe context of a palette entry which was set via PaletteEntryBuilder.context(Object).
    Names.TARGET_BOBusiness Object handler (PaletteEntryBuilder.creation() entries only)The business object of the target container. Must not be modified. Changes are not guaranteed to be persisted.
    Names.SOURCE_BOBusiness Object handler (PaletteEntryBuilder.connectionCreation() entries only)The business object of the source of the connection.
    Names.DESTINATION_BOBusiness Object handler (PaletteEntryBuilder.connectionCreation() entries only)The business object of the destination of the connection.
    See Also:
    CanCreate, GetPaletteEntries
